{"session_id":"svc-1780545671932402322","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-04T04:01:14.993998597Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-fab52595-20260604T040006-0423693b","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-fab52595\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eregistry: three-layer plugin lookup precedence (project → global → baked-in)\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM (Principle 2 of epic ddx-602ae31a)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Runtime plugin/persona resolution must consult three layers in priority order so that a project-local install always wins, a machine-wide global install is used when no project copy exists, and the baked-in default ddx plugin is the last resort. Without a single authoritative resolver, the new --global install surface (sibling beads) has nothing to resolve against and project vs global precedence is undefined.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/registry/resolve.go:29 `ResolvePlugin` is the resolution entry point; cli/internal/registry/resolve.go:15 `GlobalPluginDir` derives the global tier path from ddxroot.GlobalDir(). These must implement and be test-pinned to the precedence order: \u0026lt;project\u0026gt;/.ddx/plugins/\u0026lt;name\u0026gt; (or ddxroot.Path()/plugins/\u0026lt;name\u0026gt; in convention mode) → ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u0026lt;name\u0026gt; → baked-in (defaultplugin.FS(), valid only for name==\u0026#34;ddx\u0026#34;). The precedence ordering is currently unverified by test, so a regression that flips global ahead of project would go undetected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;1. Ensure ResolvePlugin stats the project path first (via the projectRoot arg, which routes through ddxroot.Path() for in-tree vs convention), returning layer==\u0026#34;project\u0026#34; when present.\u0026#xA;2. Fall back to ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u0026lt;name\u0026gt;, returning layer==\u0026#34;global\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;3. Fall back to baked-in, returning layer==\u0026#34;baked-in\u0026#34; with empty path, only for the \u0026#34;ddx\u0026#34; plugin; otherwise return a not-found error.\u0026#xA;4. Add focused table tests for the precedence and fallback behavior.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- The `ddx install`/`ddx update` --global CLI surface (sibling bead: install/update --global).\u0026#xA;- `ddx init` lazy-resolution and umbrella setup (sibling bead: init --global).\u0026#xA;- `ddx doctor` two-layer reporting and spec/docs updates (sibling bead: doctor + docs).\u0026#xA;- Migrating ~/.config/ddx/ legacy paths if any exist (likely none today).\u0026#xA;- Agent-harness path discovery beyond Claude Code and Codex.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEPS\u0026#xA;ddx-06cbaa90 (ddx home resolution) — project-tier resolution routes through ddxroot.Path() and the global tier through ddxroot.GlobalDir(); both must be agreed-on before this lands.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestPluginLookup_PrefersProjectOverGlobal asserts that when both the project path and ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/global/plugins/\u0026lt;name\u0026gt; contain the plugin, ResolvePlugin returns the project path with layer==\u0026#34;project\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;2. TestPluginLookup_FallsBackToGlobal asserts that when the project copy is absent but the global copy exists, ResolvePlugin returns the global path with layer==\u0026#34;global\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;3. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/registry/... green.\u0026#xA;4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:config, area:plugin, kind:feature, phase:3, initiative:zero-footprint, principle:skills-personas, triage:no-changes-unjustified\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-937de9fc\" base-rev=\"15f418c5e2466ddca0f0d117a6799780d62bd51d\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260604T040006-0423693b\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-fab52595-20260604T040006-0423693b/.ddx/executions/20260604T040006-0423693b/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-fab52595-20260604T040006-0423693b/.ddx/executions/20260604T040006-0423693b/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/Mac